main event: An unidentified flying object was observed visually and on radar over a specific location.
interesting points: The object was flying at an elevation of 20 degrees on a heading of 315 degrees, and was described as a bright white object with no sound.
The object disappeared into the clouds at an azimuth of 020 degrees.
The sighting was considered a possible satellite pass, but the data was not recognized as civilian.
Further radar observations indicated the object was visible for approximately 2 minutes, crossing the northern sky from 300 degrees true to 020 degrees true at a constant position angle.
Multiple government and military entities were involved in the reporting and analysis of this UFO sighting.
sighted object: A bright white object in the sky
